<body>
  <div class="brand"><img src="/static/lumen-crest.png" alt="Lumen"><strong>Lumen IT Solutions</strong></div>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="muted">Last updated: <%= updated %></p>

  <p>This policy explains how <strong>Lumen IT Solutions</strong> ("Lumen", "we", "us") handles personal data through our customer portal and service desk at <strong>portal.lumenmsp.co.uk</strong>, including communications received by email, WhatsApp and Microsoft Teams.</p>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>Lumen IT Solutions is a UK managed service provider. For any privacy question or data request, contact us at <a href="mailto:support@lumenmsp.co.uk">support@lumenmsp.co.uk</a>.</p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <p>When you contact our service desk or are supported by us, we may process: your name and the contact details you use to reach us (email address, phone/mobile number, WhatsApp number, Teams identity); the content of your messages and support tickets; details of the devices and services we support for your organisation; and basic technical metadata about each message (timestamps, delivery status).</p>

  <h2>How we use it</h2>
  <p>We use this information solely to provide and manage IT support and the related services you or your organisation have engaged us for — raising and resolving support tickets, replying to you on the channel you contacted us through, keeping a record of the work carried out, and managing quotes, invoices and contracts. We do not use WhatsApp, email or Teams messages for marketing.</p>

  <h2>WhatsApp messaging</h2>
  <p>If you message our business WhatsApp number, your message and number are received into our service desk to create or update a support ticket, and we reply through the WhatsApp Business Platform (Meta). Meta processes WhatsApp messages in line with its own terms; see the <a href="https://www.whatsapp.com/legal/business-policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">WhatsApp Business Messaging Policy</a>.</p>

  <h2>Lawful basis</h2>
  <p>We process this data to perform our contract with you or your organisation, and for our legitimate interest in providing and supporting our services. Where required, we rely on your consent, which you may withdraw at any time.</p>

  <h2>Sharing</h2>
  <p>We do not sell personal data. We share data only with the service providers that operate our platform (for example Microsoft for email/Teams and Meta for WhatsApp), and where we are legally required to do so.</p>

  <h2>Retention</h2>
  <p>We keep support records for as long as needed to provide our services and to meet legal, accounting and contractual obligations, after which they are deleted or anonymised.</p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>You have the right to access, correct or request deletion of your personal data, and to object to or restrict its processing. To exercise these rights, email <a href="mailto:support@lumenmsp.co.uk">support@lumenmsp.co.uk</a>. You may also complain to the UK Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>We may update this policy from time to time; the latest version will always be available at this page.</p>
</body>
</html>
